Text: Horford's lay-up pushes the Hawks lead back to 14. He now has 18 pts and 13 reb.
There seem to be a lot of faulty parachutes for the the Chick-fil-A cows tonight...
Joe came out on fire this half. He now has 25 pts as the Hawks push the lead to 81-58
Tri-Captains are getting the job done tonight. Joe, Josh and Al combined for 38 pts, 19 reb and 9 ast in the first half. Hawks lead 60-43.
Joe's jumper give them 60 in the first half. That is tied for the fourth highest of the season.
Joe is aggressive on defense tonight. He already has two clean steals that have led to points at the other end...
Hawks are dominating the stat sheet right now... 25-11 on the boards, 34-28 pts in the paint and (most importantly) a 54-41 lead
Amar'e was put on kiss cam and responds with the Mutombo finger waggle
Marvin gets it done... takes it hard to the hole and draws a foul from Amar'e. Hawks lead 47-35 with 5 min left in the half.
Hawks trying to go right at Stoudemire with Horford. It would be big to get Amar'e with 3 fouls
Horford well on his way to a double-double... in the first half. He has 8pts, 7reb with 8 minutes left
Hawks lead 30-12 after 1Q. Jamal has 9, Smoove has 8, but the real story is the 17-8 rebounding advantage.
Jamal is up to nine points as the Hawks looked like the Showtime Lakers from the 80's for a few plays. ATL leads 28-21
It's always good to see Jamal hit his first 3-ptr... no matter how deep it is. Hawks lead 21-17.
Hawks aren't shooting great, but board-work (Rebound advantage 14-4) has them ahead early, 18-15.
Hawks starting with the "athletic" line-up tonight against the Knicks: Mike, Joe, Marvin, Josh and Al... tip-off is just moments away
